{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-9b0494fba07c",
  "content": "## Decisions\n\n### D72: Cross-File Import Resolution via Cargo.toml Module Tree\n- **Decision:** Parse `Cargo.toml` + `mod` declarations to build `RustModuleMap`, use it in `resolve_rust_module_path()`\n- **Scope:** `corvia-adapter-git` crate\n- **Rationale:** Current implementation returns current file for `crate::`/`super::` paths, creating self-loops. Full module tree resolution is the only way to correctly resolve Rust module paths to file paths.\n\n\n### D73: Markdown AST Cross-References via pulldown-cmark\n- **Decision:** Parse markdown with `pulldown-cmark` to extract code spans, links, and code blocks as `\"references\"` relations\n- **Scope:** `corvia-kernel` crate (`MarkdownChunker`)\n- **Rationale:** ~600 markdown chunks are graph-isolated. Docs heavily reference code paths and types. AST-based parsing is more precise than regex.\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-04-m3.4-graph-edge-improvements-design.md",
